meanings.sent1: The city had an overdeveloped skyline with too many tall buildings.
meanings.sent2: Her overdeveloped sense of responsibility often led her to take on more than she could handle.
meanings.sent3: The cake was so overdeveloped with frosting that it looked like a mountain of sugar.
meanings.sent4: His overdeveloped muscles made him look like a superhero.
meanings.sent5: The garden was overdeveloped with colorful flowers, creating a vibrant display.

meanings.definition: Having developed beyond a normal or desirable level.
meanings.sent1: The overdeveloped fruit was too ripe to eat.
meanings.sent2: The overdeveloped technology was difficult for the older generation to understand.
meanings.sent3: The overdeveloped puppy was so energetic that it ran circles around the room.
meanings.sent4: Her overdeveloped sense of smell could detect even the faintest scents.
meanings.sent5: The overdeveloped storm caused widespread damage across the region.
